Thomas Analysis

Thomas Schindler

29 November 2017

Background

Here I focus on data analysis sampled during Summer School 2017 in Agali forest. Any collected data belong to greenhouse gas emissions by grey alder stems during the experiment phase. Basically, the experiment consisted of three periods - before, during, and afterartificial irrigation of the forest. There are two groups of stem chambers, one located at the irrigation area (Tree 01 - 08, 12), the control group consists of trees 09-11. Further, the stem chambers are located on three heights. Exceptions are made at trees: 01, 05, 07, and 10 where chambers are situated at the bottom level only.

Libraries to load

library(tidyverse)
library(tidyr)
library(ggthemes)
library(xtable)
library(ggplot2)
library(stringr)
library(scales)
library(cowplot)

library(dplyr)

N2O Data Import

  • Select my file and read data into dat dataframe
  • File contains N20 fluxes for the SummerSchool irrigation experiment only.
  • For extended time slots, another file (see below) will be used.
dat<- read.csv("n2oR.csv", header = TRUE)

Data are still in wrong format (wide instead of long)

Thus, original data table needs to be converted /gathered - library tidyr to be added to library list at the beginning

The arguments to gather(): - data: Data object - key: Name of new key column (made from names of data columns) - value: Name of new value column - : Names of source columns that contain values - factor_key: Treat the new key column as a factor (instead of character vector)

Re-Organising Data Colums, experimental sites

Zero level, experimental site

  n2o0 <- gather(dat, "olevel", "flux", Tree1h0:Tree12h0, factor_key=TRUE)

N2O Boxplots from Experimental Site, no control spots, Level 0/80/170 cm

  e1 <- ggplot(n2o0, 
              aes(x=Sampled,
                  y=flux))
  e1 <- e1 + 
        geom_boxplot(fill="blue", alpha=0.2) + 
          ggtitle("N2O, Level 0cm") +
          labs(x="Sampling Dates", y="N2O flux") +
          theme(plot.title = element_text(family = "Trebuchet MS", color="#666666", face="bold", size=18, hjust=0)) +
          theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
          scale_y_continuous(name="flux in myg/m-2 h-1", limits=c(0, 20))

The arguments to gather(): - data: Data object - key: Name of new key column (made from names of data columns) - value: Name of new value column - : Names of source columns that contain values - factor_key: Treat the new key column as a factor (instead of character vector)

CH4 Boxplots from Experimental Site, no control spots, Level 0/80/170 cm

  ch1 <- ggplot(ch40, 
              aes(x=Sampled,
                  y=flux))
  ch1 <- ch1 + 
        geom_boxplot(fill="blue", alpha=0.2) + 
          ggtitle("CH4, Level 0cm") +
          labs(x="Sampling Dates", y="CH4 flux") +

Data are still in wrong format (wide instead of long)

Thus, original data table needs to be converted /gathered - library tidyr to be added to library list at the beginning

The arguments to gather(): - data: Data object - key: Name of new key column (made from names of data columns) - value: Name of new value column - : Names of source columns that contain values - factor_key: Treat the new key column as a factor (instead of character vector)

Re-Organising Data Colums, experimental sites

N2O Night Boxplots from Experimental Site, no control spots, Level 0/80/170 cm

  n1 <- ggplot(n2on0, 
              aes(x=Sampled,
                  y=flux))
  n1 <- n1 + 
        geom_boxplot(fill="blue", alpha=0.2) + 
          ggtitle("N2O Night, Level 0cm") +
          labs(x="Sampling Dates", y="N2O flux") +
          theme(plot.title = element_text(family = "Trebuchet MS", color="#666666", face="bold", size=18, hjust=0)) +
          theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
          scale_y_continuous(name="flux in myg/m-2 h-1", limits=c(0, 20)) 
  n1

  n2 <- ggplot(n2on80, 
              aes(x=Sampled,
                  y=flux))
  n2 <- n2 + 
        geom_boxplot(fill="blue", alpha=0.2) + 
          ggtitle("N2O Night, Level 80cm") +
          labs(x="Sampling Dates", y="N2O flux") +
          theme(plot.title = element_text(family = "Trebuchet MS", color="#666666", face="bold", size=18, hjust=0)) +
          theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
          scale_y_continuous(name="flux in myg/m-2 h-1", limits=c(0, 20)) 
  n2
